reviews.review_text: 1990-0710 This one definately beats my old Aud ,which sounded like a giant tiolet flushing.Maybe not the best quality,but not as murky as the board.
vg w/eq with eq, this recording is very good. check out the sbd for tons of accounts of the show and the weather. the music itself is very good: strong desire from the band throughout.

thanks! Thanks for uploading! This was a great show. It was super hot all day and then this big black cloud hovered right above the stadium and there was lightening and thunder and the power went out during promised land as people were sliding down this mud hill.
It's a great recording but of course our computer speakers can never capture the same sound as it was live. I remember the sound being extra crispy that night between pittsburg and dc shows.

Great tape, thanks I needed an aud of this, Mark's fob is right on!
I wager this is one of the best Phil inspired other ones post 75.
There's at least 4 other one rips up the stairs here.
Tell me otherwise if you have suggestions,
AZ
